1. Real Data & Services (full stack)

Everything live вҖ” Go backend, PostgreSQL, Redis, real agent data.

cd xcloak-platform
docker compose up -d
# Frontend: http://localhost:3000
# Backend:  http://localhost:8080

Login with your real credentials. Data comes from your actual database.

---
2. Demo Data + Real Backend (seeded DB)

Go backend running but pre-seeded with fake demo data. Useful for testing backend features with realistic data.

cd xcloak-platform
docker compose -f docker-compose.demo.yml up -d

# Seed demo data (first time only)
docker exec xcloak-demo-backend ./seed-demo

# Frontend: http://localhost:3000
# Visit /demo to start a session

All API calls go through the real Go backend, but the database has synthetic alerts, agents, incidents, etc.

---
3. Demo Data, No Backend (static вҖ” what we built)

Pure Next.js, zero backend required. All data is baked into the JS bundle.

cd xcloak-platform/frontend

# Dev (hot-reload, slower start):
NEXT_PUBLIC_DEMO_ONLY=true npm run dev

# Production (fast, what Netlify runs):
NEXT_PUBLIC_DEMO_ONLY=true npm run build
NEXT_PUBLIC_DEMO_ONLY=true npx next start -p 3333

# Visit http://localhost:3333/demo

No Docker, no database, no Go binary needed. All 200 alerts, 30 playbook executions, 120 sigma rules etc. come from lib/demo-data/data.json via the static router.

